    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but isnt \"market forces\" just a fancy way of saying my shop might have to close if i can't keep up? it feels like the people pushing for these hikes don't really get how it works for someone actually running a business in a small town. why does it always feel like the policy is designed for big corporations that can handle it, while leaving the little guys to just deal with the fallout?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
